  "chapter": {
    "number": 14,
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "content": [
          "A Call to Repentance"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 1,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Return, O Israel, to the LORD your God,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "for you have stumbled by your iniquity.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 2,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Bring your confessions",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and return to the LORD.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "Say to Him: “Take away all our iniquity",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and receive us graciously,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "that we may present",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "the fruit of our lips.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "noteId": 2508
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 3,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Assyria will not save us,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "nor will we ride on horses.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "We will never again say, ‘Our gods!’",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "to the work of our own hands.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "lineBreak": true
          },
          {
            "text": "For in You the fatherless find compassion.”",
            "poem": 1
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "content": [
          "A Promise of God’s Blessing"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 4,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "I will heal their apostasy;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "I will freely love them,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "for My anger has turned away from them.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 5,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "I will be like the dew to Israel;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "he will blossom like the lily",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "and take root like the cedars of Lebanon.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 6,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "His shoots will sprout,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and his splendor will be like the olive tree,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "his fragrance like the cedars of Lebanon.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 7,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "They will return and dwell in his shade;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "they will grow grain and blossom like the vine.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "His renown will be like the wine of Lebanon.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 8,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "O Ephraim,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "noteId": 2509
          },
          {
            "text": "what have I to do",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "anymore with idols?",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "It is I who answer and watch over him.",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "I am like a flourishing cypress;",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "noteId": 2510
          },
          {
            "text": "your fruit comes from Me.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 9,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Whoever is wise, let him understand these things;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "whoever is discerning, let him know them.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "For the ways of the LORD are right,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and the righteous walk in them",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "but the rebellious stumble in them.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      }
    ],
    "footnotes": [
      {
